getByDate

public R getByDate(Currency currency,
                   java.util.Calendar date)
Description copied from interface: RateParametersDAO
gets past date rateparameters for currencies. If you want present ratepareameters for currency, just use currency.getXRateParameters(). This method is only useful if you need to get rateparameters of a past date which are now not valid any more on the currency.

getByPeriod

public java.util.List<R> getByPeriod(Currency currency,
                                     Period period)
Description copied from interface: RateParametersDAO
gets a list of all rateParameters that were valid during the specified period, in reversed date order - this means ordered by enabledSince, the latest entities first.

Specified by:
getByPeriod in interface RateParametersDAO<R extends RateParameters>
period - despite any settings on the period, this is always with beginDate exclusive, and endDate inclusive, because RateParameters are defined with beginDate inclusive and endDate exclusive. For the same reason, the useTime flag in period is ignored, and period is always treated as if this flag was set to true.
